    <item>
      <title>"Heart of..." line</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&amp;message.id=4397#M4397</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Is there any chance we could possibly get our "Heart of..." line (Heart of Stone, Flame, Vapor, Ice) separated so that they are each on their own individual timer? At this point in the game, with some of them eclipsed by better choices (like Silent Casting, the Fickle Fire recourse, etc.), it would make them much more viable, since currently it's really a toss-up between either using only Heart of Flame or using only Heart of Stone...the others see very little, if any, use due to the tied timers. If absolutely necessary, perhaps we could place stacking restrictions on them so you cannot use more than one at a time, if balance issues are a concern. &lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;-Koz&lt;/P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Oshran said, "At this time there is no plan to seperate these into different timers.&amp;nbsp; All of the "Heart of" buffs are pretty good (even if some are better in more situations then others). Currently mages can only have these buffs active for a maximum of 90 seconds out of every 22 minutes (6% of the time).&amp;nbsp; Assuming we make the buffs non-stackable, then splitting the reuse timers will enable mages to have these buffs active for 360 seconds out of every 22 minutes (27 % of the time).&amp;nbsp; That means they will be able to utilize these relatively powerful buffs much more often (roughly 4.5 times as often) over any given period of time.&amp;nbsp; That's too much a jump in power and it also removes the interesting gameplay choice inherent in the AA set itself… 'which buff do you want on you given your current situation knowing that your choice will cause you to lose the other 3 options?'"&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;-Koz&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2006 21:55:26 GMT</pubDate>
