    <item>
      <title>Moving forward (re: Top Ten)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&amp;message.id=4358#M4358</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;NOTE: This is a copy/paste of a post I made at the &lt;a target="_blank" href="http://eq1.eqsummoners.com/viewtopic.php?t=26026"&gt;Mage Tower&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;First of all, please excuse the overall tone of this post, which I'm sure will be a bit stern, and perhaps even a bit obnoxious. The following is a trademark &amp;quot;good thing&amp;quot;, but I want to make sure everyone is on the same page as far as expectations go. You'll understand why when you read it.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Some of you may have heard whisperings about this already- the proverbial cat is out of the bag on some of the class forums. Basically, we're going to be phasing out the idea of the Top Ten lists. It's no secret that, by and large, they have not worked for a while (or, depending on how you want to look at it, they worked just fine...at first, they were more about addressing bugs, and those generally got resolved quickly, but lately, they're more of a &amp;quot;wish list&amp;quot; compilation, which does not lend itself to the same type of speedy resolution/answers).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We've (&lt;strong&gt;tentatively&lt;/strong&gt;) decided to go with a &amp;quot;question of the week&amp;quot; format, though I shudder at the idea of calling it that. In any event, we'll (&lt;strong&gt;tentatively&lt;/strong&gt;) be submitting a question each week, and Kytherea will forward them on to their respective devs, who will respond to them and send the responses back to Kytherea, who will relay them back to us.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font size="6"&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" href="http://dictionary.reference.com/search?q=tentatively"&gt;TENTATIVELY.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Now, the rest of the disclaimers, because again- I don't want any false expectations and disappointments at any point. Well, I don't want any false expectations and disappointments that you can blame on &lt;em&gt;me&lt;/em&gt; at any point.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Above, I said we've decided to go with a &amp;quot;question of the week&amp;quot; format. The key word there is &amp;quot;question&amp;quot;- NOT &amp;quot;answer&amp;quot;. &lt;strong&gt;I'm not going to promise that we'll get an answer every week.&lt;/strong&gt; Even if we get one answer a month, that's more than we have been getting. Keep that in mind.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Last week, 17 questions were asked (one correspondent did not submit a question), and 9 responses were received. That's technically more than half. I think that's a very good start, but when the time comes that &lt;strong&gt;our&lt;/strong&gt; question does not receive a response right away- and that time WILL come- I don't want people to be disheartened. &lt;strong&gt;There's always next week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Different questions require different devs in order to receive an answer. Spell questions go to Prathun, AA questions go to Oshran, tradeskill questions go to Ngreth, etc. &lt;strong&gt;It's inevitable that sometimes those devs will have time to answer our questions, and sometimes they will not.&lt;/strong&gt; Right now, for example, Oshran has respectfully informed us that he's just too swamped to give any AA questions the time they deserve, and will probably start to be able to accept questions in June or July. Personally, I think that's great- not only has a dev told us he's just too busy to entertain our questions at the moment, but he's also given us a (&lt;strong&gt;tentative&lt;/strong&gt;) idea of when he WILL be able to. Again, a good thing.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="6"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keep in mind that the answers will not always be what you want to hear.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/font&gt;I cannot stress this enough.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Anyway...last week (the first week of May) was our first attempt at this. Because we were still keeping the idea quiet at that time, since we didn't know how it would work out, I chose the question myself. &lt;strong&gt;In the future, I will give you an opportunity to submit questions, and I will pull from that list as needed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;My first question was for Rapaz:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;em&gt;At the Fan Faire, it was mentioned that certain aspects of the UI were probably going to undergo an overhaul in the near future. Of particular concern to mages would be the addition of visible damage messages from things such as pet weapon procs, pet spells, pet spell resists, etc., as well as corresponding filters for these options; and, of course, a complete overhaul of the pet window, adding buttons for newer commands such as /pet hold, /pet focus, /pet no cast, with a corresponding status window to show &amp;quot;at a glance&amp;quot; information on the current status of the pet, along with other conveniences such as percentage-based health information and, ideally, a pet inventory that would allow us to manage pet equipment easily.&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;I mentioned some of this at the Fan Faire in my various discussions with the devs, and it's my understanding that these are all things mages will most likely see in the future, with the exception of one thing: the pet inventory. I didn't get a chance to mention this then, but it's something that's often requested within the community.&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;Would we be able to get an estimated timeline for these additions, as well as an idea of how feasible something like a pet inventory would be? Even if these changes were to go in gradually, instead of all at once, they would go a long way toward making the game more &amp;quot;pet-friendly&amp;quot;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Rapaz answered with:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am definitely familiar with some of these requests and not so familiar with others. They sound like good ideas to me, but I do not currently have a timeframe for any of these just yet.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Which may not be the response some of you were hoping for, but it's a response. And the pet inventory idea was not blatantly shot down (to be perfectly honest, that surprised me- I've always considered a pet inventory to be a huge pipe dream that probably isn't even possible).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;This week, I decided to yield to the correspondents who did not receive a response last week. It's fair, although it may not make some of you happy. But there will be plenty of time for our questions in the future, with this new format.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So...for the next couple of weeks or so, I'm going to continue to submit personal questions, and share the responses with you. These will likely be questions that I had prepared for the FF, but didn't get a chance to bring up. I'm doing this because we're still in the experimental phase of this method. After a few weeks- assuming that we decide to adopt this format &amp;quot;officially&amp;quot;- I'll open up a thread for everyone to post their questions.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Personally, I think this is a really good idea. I just hate calling it a &amp;quot;question of the week&amp;quot;, because that sets the wrong expectations, which makes me nervous. Again, even just one response a &lt;strong&gt;month&lt;/strong&gt; is better than what we were getting with the Top Ten lists. &lt;strong&gt;Just do my nerves a favour and keep your expectations realistic, please!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-Koz&lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Sat, 15 Jul 2006 20:40:30 GMT</pubDate>
