      <title>My idea for Magician Utility</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&amp;message.id=4342#M4342</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;I am posting this on the mage boards to make an attempt to provide a usefull comment on a way to add a unique ability to magicians.  Please do not add rants to my post, They have all been heard before.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Desirability for a certain class is what that class can do to contribute to the other classes making them better.  Currently there are only three Magician spells with this utility.  CoTH: useful timesaver but otherwise pointless.  Mod Rod: outdated and doesnt scale well with other classes buffs.  And Damage shield line which while usefull, its not going to win over many people.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Instead I would like to see a new summoned item line of spells that create targetable clicky items with buffs that effect the hard cap of the user for a set amount of time and the result from summoning them would be a determinal spell cast on the magician for the same amount of time and effect.  ie. Magician casts spell Orb of health-  -1000 hp of magicians cap for 10 min.  This would create a clickable item for the targeted person that when clicked would give them a buff that increases their hp cap by 1000 for 10 min.  It should stack with all current buffs but not stack with itself so it doesnt get overpowering if say ten mages were to give one tank ten of said item and he gets 10k hp buff.  This could easily scale for all magician levels 1 - 70 and beyond simply by changeing the effect to one of the less important stats like int, wis, dex, resists, or the amount of the cap, possibly even increaseing the duriation as the magician reaches a higher level.  However these summoned items should only modify the caps and should not heal the person or regenerate mana, Keeping people from wanting them just for a quick shot of mana or a quick heal.  Also these items would need to be lore to keep the magician in the loop instead of one mage sitting in pok selling them eliminateing the need of the magician but everyone still getting the advantage of it.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Thats all I have for my big idea for now.  Post more ideas.  I like reading them and I would like to see something besides just adding DPS to our class.  Yes we are a DPS class but we are not the best so something must bridge that gap. What is it to you?&lt;/div&gt;</description>
