      <title>Elemental Swarm &amp; Servant of Ro are not usable in high end raids.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&amp;message.id=4293#M4293</link>
      <description>Many new raid encounters are about DPS control, in other words DPS at the wrong moment and raid is wiped.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;How do Servant of Ro and Elemental Swarm fit in this Raid pattern? The answer is that these AA's only effect is to wipe raids.&lt;br&gt;This is because both these aas have &amp;quot;low&amp;quot; dps and &amp;quot;high&amp;quot; duration, both can last up to 1 minute.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Mages are a DPS class and these should be our DPS disciplines but we can not use them as they are uncontrollable and dangerous. Is this fair? Does it make sense?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What about making these aas last 18 seconds and increase the dps leaving the total damage unchanged? That would give more usefulness to these aas. What about changing elemental swarm(9 mini pets) into 1 fat pet which can survive AE? What about removing kick and bash from Elemental Swarm so Raid leaders stop banning this aa cause the push wipes the raids?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Thank you for reading this.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
